Nothing special about their ramen's taste, it's not even average it's below average.
Obviously, it is not the #1 halal ramen beef in Japan that was a lie.
Their restaurant design is dull with bunch of posters.

Highly recommended

reviews.snippet:
I ate the spesial set for Breeze ramen during Summer, I got:
- bowl of dry ramen with 1 slice of wagyu
- 2 pcs of wagyu sushi
- 2 pcs of karaage
- 1 bowl of shaved ice (I chose Lychee Syrup on that)

and trust me you won't regret it!!!
since it is Summer edition so I want to try the dry ramen style, it turned out the ramen was cold yet fresh and not soggy, with a unique "refreshing" taste with some condiments and the seasoning just amazing for the summer!

their service also nice and will welcome you with smiles and greetings
also the prayer room was more than enough for 2 people with proper ablution place.
